    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d155fn1">This message was sent by Roosevelt to Eisenhower,
                        in telegram <gloss target="#t_Freedom1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Freedom</hi>
                        </gloss> 8961, May 27, 1943, 4 p.m., for delivery to <gloss
                            target="#t_Churchill1">Churchill</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-27">May 27,
                            1943</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. We were all very happy to hear this afternoon that you have safely completed
                    the second leg of the trip. I have given the one sentence announcement of the
                    end of the conferences to the Press.<note n="2" xml:id="d155fn2">For the
                        statement by Roosevelt, see <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> I miss you much. It was a highly successful meeting in every way and
                    proved that it was well timed and necessary.</p>
            </div>
